# The approve-claude token step — whose logic lives INSIDE bin/agent-vault-provision
# (the Claude-OAuth human-gate / proposal-approve path, L272-409), NOT a separate
# script — writes a BLANK Claude credential: the resulting CLAUDE_OAUTH value is
# empty. Performing the SAME approval manually through the broker web interface
# stores a non-empty credential, which proves upstream issuance is correct and
# localizes the defect to the script's token CAPTURE/WRITEBACK. This scenario PINS
# the correct behavior: the scripted approve-claude step captures the issued token
# and writes a NON-EMPTY CLAUDE_OAUTH credential value (no blank writeback). Single
# behavior: faithful non-empty writeback of the captured token.
